Orchestrates leaf-up context summarization across a codebase, executing an LLM-powered pipeline that reads source files, applies prompt templates loaded at runtime from `prompts/`, and writes `.ctx` outputs.

The module structure enforces strict layering: `cli` parses argv and I/O, `runner` coordinates the core orchestration logic (pure), and `fs`/`agent` are seams for I/O and LLM interaction. Prompts are never embedded—they're loaded dynamically at runtime, keeping prompts and code separate for independent iteration. The user message contains only dynamic data (file paths, content); static instructions live in prompt files. `intent.md` is never written to disk.

Public modules: `agent` (LLM interaction), `cli` (argv/stdio), `cpath` (context path utilities), `error` (error types), `fs` (filesystem operations), `progress` (progress reporting), `runner` (core logic). `rollup_input` is private (internal to runner's workflow). This is the entry point to the summarizer; callers invoke `runner` directly for programmatic use.